text: Aurea is a Latin female name meaning "golden". Aurea may refer to: * Auria, queen of Pamplona in the 10th century * Aurea (singer) (born 1987), a Portuguese soul singer * Aurea of Ostia, 3rd-century Italian martyr * Áurea Cruz (born 1982), a Puerto Rican volleyball player * Áurea of San Millán (1043–1070), a Spanish saint * Aurea, Auburn University golden eagle, flies in stadium before football games Category:Latin feminine given names
title: Aurea (given name)
